shared_text:
Spring Hill High School Comfort Closet
August 26 at 12:06 PM ·

Hello! Spring Hill High School Leaders' Core and student volunteers have created a Comfort Closet for our students in need. Our goals are to provide hygiene products and gently used clothing. We greatly appreciate any donations and support!

Current wishlist:
-Drawstring backpacks
-Clothing racks
-Gently used clothing and shoes (for girls and boys, all adult sizes)
-New underwear and socks (for girls and boys, all adult sizes)
-Hygiene products (such as soap, shampoo, razors, tampons, toothbrushes, toothpaste, etc.)

Donations can be dropped off at the high school office or email edrueckhammer@shisd.net to arrange a pick up.

Parents of all Primary students:

Letters will be mailed tomorrow, August 5th with teacher assignments.
Teachers will be personally contacting you to set up a time for your in person Meet The Teacher on August 12th, 13th, or 14th. August 17th will be the beginning date for all students to return to school in person or virtually.
Please note that this plan is specific to the Primary and Intermediate campuses. Junior High and High School students have a different start up plan for the 12th, 13th, and 14th. You can find more information on our district website.

Spring Hill ISD
July 21 at 4:44 PM ·

Panther Nation,
Below is a link to Spring Hill ISD's plan to re-open school for the 2020-2021 school year. As we continue to receive information and make updates, we will highlight any changes that are made to this document for future reference. An FAQ will be released tomorrow that will hopefully answer many of your questions.

We are in the process of receiving our final shipments of Chromebooks that will meet our 1:1 goal of providing every student with their own technology device.

Thank you for your patience as we strive to provide the safest learning environment for our students and staff. We look forward to a great year...Go Panthers

Thank you for your patience as we strive to provide the safest learning environment for our students and staff. We look forward to a great year...Go Panthers

Spring Hill ISD
June 3 at 10:32 AM ·

Spring Hill Parents,

We are all looking forward to fall when we can hopefully all return to school. With this in mind, we want to remind ALL parents, and especially parents of incoming Pre-K, Kindergarten and 7th grade students to contact your student’s physician and ensure that your child is up to date on state required vaccines. If they are not, please contact your student’s physician and make time to have these vaccines administered before the 2020-2021 school year begins. Also, please make sure to provide your student’s campus nurse with an updated vaccination record once we are able to come together again.

Until then, stay safe and healthy by continuing proper social distancing, frequent handwashing of at least 20 seconds with soap and water, covering coughs and sneezes with a tissue or the bend of your elbow, and proper disinfecting of frequently touched objects and surfaces.

Spring Hill ISD Nursing Department

shared_text:
Spring Hill High School Theatre
May 15 at 8:45 PM ·

Dear students,
It is with great trepidation that I have made the decision to retire. After 32 years of teaching and mentoring young people, the time has come. I know you are asking why my parents are requiring more attention and care than I can give working full time. As much as I love my job and all of you my family is very important to me. I want each of you to know how much I have enjoyed working with you. I will still be around to help out and support you. I hope you will all understand and will continue to be a part of the theatre program. It’s not over it’s just the next adventure. I have been looking for someone to recommend and I believe I have found a great new director with lots of energy and passion. Please give this person the respect and devotion that you have given me.
I love you all.

Mrs. Smith

post_text:
Deadline approaching fast. Get your pictures submitted.

All pictures MUST be:
** edited and ready to go,
** saved in a .jpeg format,
** and sent as email attachments (NOT in the "body" portion of the email) to springhillseniorcelebration@gmail.com.

If this sounds confusing to you then you should simply post your edited, ready to go photos to the Senior Celebration Facebook page.

ONE baby picture -
ONE in-between picture -
& ONE Senior picture for each student.

Be sure to include student's name listed/spelled as you want it displayed in the slide show/video

Please do not send four individual photos - if you do, three pictures will be picked at random.

Spring Hill ISD
March 19 at 8:26 PM ·

Panther Nation,
We would like to recognize Janet Albright, Susan Lumbert, Joleen Thurman and Marissa Aburto for going above the call of duty, so that we can provide free meals to our kids during this school closure! We appreciate you all so much!

Beginning Monday, March 23, we will be providing free meals to kids 18 years and under at a second location - Spring Hill Leaders Core Park, 3513 Denson Rd, Monday - Friday from 11:30 am - 12:30 pm.

We will continue to provide free meals to kids 18 years and under from the Primary campus Monday - Friday from 11:00 am - 12:30 pm.

Students must be present to receive free meals. For additional information, please email contact@shisd.net.

March 19 at 9:29 AM ·

The SHJH faculty have been working since Monday to move all of our lessons to an on-line format. All students can access their core content and begin completing lessons in Google Classroom on Monday, March 23. All of our students should be able to access their Google Classrooms from home as this is a program that many of our teachers use regularly. The District is developing a plan for students that do not have access to a computer or the Internet.

Please go do the district's site for in-home learning here https://sites.google.com/shisd.net/shisd-in-home-learning/home

Please email dlynch@shisd.net or your teacher with any questions.

post_text: Such a sweet moment shared between a SH kindergartener and a SH Junior!! #kindnessmatters #sweetkids
shared_text:
Sara Canter McKinley is at Air U Trampoline Park.
February 13 at 10:14 PM · Longview, TX ·

We were at Air U Trampoline Park this evening with friends. Eli was overtired and was having a “moment” so he sat down feeling sad... this sweet HS kid that works there immediately came and sat with him and encouraged him. It was such a small kind gesture, but says A LOT about this kids character.
If you know him or his boss at AirU, share this or tag them. We want them to know we are thankful for him!
